item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: thedavil
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: ASSET STORE
item.dc:creator: thedavil
item.content:encoded:
Welcome to the DX4D asset store.

Due to the fact that our addons use a component based model, the addons available on this site require multiple plugins to function properly. To make things simple, click the ADDON link down below and choose the addon you want to purchase. There you will find a list of all the required components for that particular addon. Just check all the boxes and click "add to cart" to purchase that addon.

Once you own a base library, you will not need to buy it again.

In the future when you buy additional addons, go into the COMPONENTS category and just buy the component for the addon you would like to purchase. As long as you own the BASE LIBRARIES required for that component you will be able to use it without buying (or installing) any other plugins.

item.title: CharacterView [component]
item.dc:creator: thedavil
item.content:encoded:
Allows you to show a view of your character on the screen. Supports various configurable views that can be used to view characters and other objects on the UI of your game. Originally designed to show a view of the player on the equipment screen that reflects changes to equipment in real-time. Could be used to build a character select screen, character creation screen, npc dialogue screens, a barber shop/tattoo shop, or even a minimap.
  • TotalCustomization (no coding required)
  • Drag and Drop installation
  • Animated Views
  • uMMORPG compatible with No Core Changes
  • UMA compatible (ummorpg requires a 3rd party addon to use UMA)
  • Update Proof! The base libraries work independently of ummorpg...this addon will not break with every update.
This is a Unity plugin specifically tailored to work with uMMORPG and UMA (neither is required). CHANGELOG V1.104.1 -optimization -separated shared code into Viewports component v1.102.1 -plugin released
item.excerpt:encoded: REQUIRES: VIEWPORTS Shows a view of any character in your game on the screen. Designed for uMMORPG and supports UMA

item.title: DialogueView [component]
item.dc:creator: thedavil
item.content:encoded:
Shows a conversation on the screen between any 2 characters in your game. A necessary plugin for story-driven games.
  • TotalCustomization (no coding required)
  • Drag and Drop installation
  • Animated Views
  • uMMORPG compatible with No Core Changes
  • UMA compatible (ummorpg requires a 3rd party addon to use UMA)
  • Update Proof! The base libraries work independently of ummorpgthis addon will not break with every update.
This is a Unity plugin to show dialogue between characters in your game. It works with uMMORPG and UMA (neither is required). This plugin is built on top of the Character View plugin...if you purchased that plugin already you can get a discount on this one. CHANGELOG V1.104.1 -optimization -separated shared code into Viewports component v1.102.1 -plugin released
item.excerpt:encoded: REQUIRES: VIEWPORTS Shows a conversation on the screen between any 2 characters in your game. A necessary plugin for story-driven games. Designed for uMMORPG and supports UMA

item.title: VIEWPORTS [library]
item.dc:creator: thedavil
item.content:encoded:
Show different views of game characters on the screen.
Originally designed to show a view of the player on the equipment screen that reflected changes to equipment in real-time. From there the plugin was extended to support various configurable views that can be used as a basis to develop a wide variety of plugins that require a view of the character or other game objects. A few examples would be a character select screen, character creation screen, npc dialogue screens, a barber shop/tattoo shop, or a minimap. It could even be used to make a plugin for trying on equipment or to show pieces of armor or other equipment in the shop.
Bottom line: It's versatile, and we're hoping to see a lot of good plugins developed using this plugin as a basis.
item.excerpt:encoded: REQUIRES: DX4DBASE Base classes used to show different views of game objects on the screen. Required for multiple plugins on this site, including "View" addons.
